<paragraph blockId="8.[151,625,1266,1326]" box="[151,295,1301,1326]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,287,1301,1326]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Figs 51–56</figureCitation>
